    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="363"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/1381: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-25T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 25, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Department’s 14, March 21, 7 p.m. Statement regarding rights of Japanese in
                    their Concession was drafted by British Consul General and accepted without
                    question or discussion by all consular representatives but I am not sure that
                    any sound basis for it can be found. I have made inquiry of the British Consul
                    General and will telegraph later if anything of value is ascertained.</p>
                <p>In view of the information contained in my 44, March 25, 11 a.m., no further
                    representations regarding this matter seem to be required at present but if they
                    should become necessary they will be based on the second paragraph of the
                    Department’s telegram under reference.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping, Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
